---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const title = "Insurance for International Physicians | Compare Expat Plans";
const description = "Health insurance guide for Physicians working internationally, covering medical positions abroad, doctor careers overseas, and global healthcare opportunities.";
const headline = "Insurance for International Physicians";
const subheadline = "Coverage solutions for Physicians working abroad, practicing medicine internationally, and pursuing careers across hospitals, clinics, and healthcare systems worldwide.";
const canonicalPath = "/guides/physician-insurance";
const heroBackgroundImage = "/images/guides/physician-insurance-hero.png";

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', label: 'Overview' },
  { id: 'coverage-needs', label: 'Coverage Needs' },
  { id: 'work-settings', label: 'Work Settings' },
  { id: 'credentials', label: 'Credentials' },
  { id: 'occupational-health', label: 'Occupational Health' },
  { id: 'work-demands', label: 'Work Demands' },
  { id: 'career-considerations', label: 'Career Considerations' },
  { id: 'faqs', label: 'FAQs' },
  { id: 'next-steps', label: 'Next Steps' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title={title}
  description={description}
  headline={headline}
  subheadline={subheadline}
  canonicalPath={canonicalPath}
  heroBackgroundImage={heroBackgroundImage}
  tocItems={tocItems}
>
  <article class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">

    <section id="overview">
      <h2>International Physician Careers</h2>
      <p>
        Physicians diagnose and treat patients, provide medical care, and serve essential healthcare functions across specialties. International medical practice offers opportunities to work in diverse healthcare systems, gain varied clinical experience, and contribute to global health.
      </p>
      <p>
        International physician opportunities exist through hospitals worldwide, international health organizations, academic medical centers, and the global need for qualified medical professionals.
      </p>
      <p>
        This guide addresses insurance considerations for Physicians working abroad across hospitals, clinics, and healthcare systems worldwide.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="coverage-needs">
      <h2>Coverage Needs for Physicians</h2>

      <ComparisonTable
        columns={[
          { key: 'need', header: 'Coverage Need' },
          { key: 'why', header: 'Why It Matters' },
          { key: 'typical', header: 'Coverage Situation?' },
        ]}
        rows={[
          { need: 'General health coverage', why: 'Professional health maintenance', typical: 'Usually employer-provided' },
          { need: 'Mental health support', why: 'High-pressure medical decisions', typical: 'Important for profession' },
          { need: 'Infectious disease coverage', why: 'Patient exposure risks', typical: 'Essential for profession' },
          { need: 'Malpractice coverage', why: 'Professional liability protection', typical: 'Critical—separate coverage' },
          { need: 'Disability coverage', why: 'Income protection', typical: 'Consider strongly' },
          { need: 'Travel coverage', why: 'Conferences and medical missions', typical: 'Often provided' },
        ]}
      />

      <h3>Professional Liability</h3>
      <p>
        Malpractice insurance is critical for physicians—this is typically separate from health insurance and must be specifically arranged for each jurisdiction of practice. International medical practice requires understanding local malpractice requirements and ensuring appropriate professional liability coverage.
      </p>
      <p>
        Disability coverage protecting income is particularly important given the lengthy training investment in medical careers. Long-term disability protection helps secure financial stability against practice-ending conditions.
      </p>

      <h3>Practice Demands</h3>
      <p>
        Medicine involves high-stakes decisions, long hours, and emotional intensity. Mental health support helps physicians manage the psychological demands of medical practice. The stress of international adaptation adds additional pressure requiring support.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-settings">
      <h2>Coverage by Work Setting</h2>

      <h3>Hospital</h3>
      <p>
        Hospital-based practice. Comprehensive hospital benefits. Shift or scheduled. Hospitals offer structure.
      </p>

      <h3>Private Practice</h3>
      <p>
        Independent medical practice. Self-arranged coverage. Autonomy. Private practice requires planning.
      </p>

      <h3>Academic Medicine</h3>
      <p>
        University medical center. Academic benefits. Research and teaching. Academic offers breadth.
      </p>

      <h3>International Organization</h3>
      <p>
        WHO, MSF, international health. Organization benefits. Global health focus. Organizations offer impact.
      </p>

      <h3>Telemedicine</h3>
      <p>
        Remote medical consultation. Variable arrangements. Location flexible. Telemedicine growing.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Coverage for Physicians"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for Physicians working abroad across hospitals, clinics, and healthcare systems worldwide."
      buttonText="Compare Physician Plans"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

    <section id="credentials">
      <h2>Credentials and Professional Recognition</h2>

      <h3>Medical License</h3>
      <p>
        Medical degree and license. Country-specific licensure. Examination may be required.
      </p>

      <h3>Specialty Certification</h3>
      <p>
        Board certification. Specialty recognition. Fellowship completion. Specialty credentials vary internationally.
      </p>

      <h3>Credential Verification</h3>
      <p>
        Degree verification. Training documentation. Reference requirements. Verification processes vary.
      </p>

      <h3>Language Proficiency</h3>
      <p>
        Patient communication. Documentation requirements. Medical language. Language requirements vary.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="occupational-health">
      <h2>Occupational Health Considerations</h2>

      <h3>Decision Stress</h3>
      <p>
        High-stakes decisions. Patient outcomes. Medical responsibility. Mental health support valuable.
      </p>

      <h3>Exposure Risks</h3>
      <p>
        Infectious disease. Sharps injuries. Patient contact. Exposure coverage essential.
      </p>

      <h3>Long Hours</h3>
      <p>
        Extended shifts. On-call demands. Night work. Wellness support relevant.
      </p>

      <h3>Physical Demands</h3>
      <p>
        Standing procedures. Surgery demands. Emergency response. Physical health matters.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="work-demands">
      <h2>Managing Work Demands</h2>

      <h3>Patient Care</h3>
      <p>
        Diagnosis and treatment. Clinical decision-making. Patient management. Care is core work.
      </p>

      <h3>Documentation</h3>
      <p>
        Medical records. Clinical notes. Legal requirements. Documentation essential.
      </p>

      <h3>Continuing Education</h3>
      <p>
        Medical knowledge currency. CME requirements. Practice evolution. Education maintains competence.
      </p>

      <h3>Team Leadership</h3>
      <p>
        Healthcare team coordination. Training supervision. Care coordination. Leadership enables care.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="career-considerations">
      <h2>Career Considerations</h2>

      <h3>Credential Complexity</h3>
      <p>
        International licensure complex. Examination requirements vary. Process can be lengthy. Research thoroughly.
      </p>

      <h3>Specialty Demand</h3>
      <p>
        Some specialties high demand globally. Others oversupplied in certain markets. Market research important.
      </p>

      <h3>Compensation Variation</h3>
      <p>
        Physician compensation varies significantly globally. Consider total package. Lifestyle factors matter.
      </p>

      <h3>Career Paths</h3>
      <p>
        Clinical practice. Administration. Research. Education. Multiple paths available.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section id="faqs">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">I'm a physician considering international work. What should I know?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Licensure requirements vary significantly. Malpractice coverage essential. Research destination thoroughly. Benefits typically provided.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Do employers provide health coverage?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Yes typically. Hospital employers comprehensive. Benefits quality varies. Verify specific offer.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">What about malpractice insurance?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Critical and separate from health insurance. Requirements vary by jurisdiction. Must arrange specifically. Essential for practice.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Do medical credentials transfer internationally?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Verification required. Examinations may be needed. Process varies significantly. Research destination requirements.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">Is disability coverage important?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Yes for income protection. Training investment significant. Career-ending injury possible. Disability coverage valuable.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mt-0 mb-2">What's the career outlook?</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
            Physician demand continues. Some specialties higher demand. International opportunities exist. Outlook generally positive.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="next-steps">
      <h2>Next Steps</h2>
      <p>
        Start by researching licensure requirements for your destination. Ensure malpractice coverage for practice jurisdiction. Consider disability coverage for income protection. Verify health coverage scope for international work.
      </p>
      <p>
        Physicians provide essential medical care worldwide. Your coverage should support medical careers—addressing practice demands, covering professional liability, and protecting you across medical practice worldwide.
      </p>
    </section>

    <CTABox
      title="Protect Your Medical Career"
      description="Compare international health plans designed for Physicians working abroad across hospitals, clinics, and healthcare systems worldwide."
      buttonText="Compare Plans Now"
      buttonHref="/"
      variant="highlight"
    />

  </article>
</PageShell>
